Austen Mcdonald from Australia performs his contemporary variation during the final of the 48th Prix de Lausanne in Montreux, Switzerland, 08 February 2020. Launched in 1973, the Prix de Lausanne is an international dance competition for young dancers aged 15 to 18. Closing the six-day event, scholarships granting free tuition in a world-renowned dance school or dance company are awarded to the best dancers out of 77 participants this year. EPA-EFE/VALENTIN FLAURAUD   Sign up for our newsletter to get the best of Maverick Life delivered to your inbox every Sunday morning at 9am. Please note you must be a Maverick Insider to comment. Sign up here or sign in if you are already an Insider.